Well, that was all. The various parts of my comparative paradise — the bedside lamp, the sleeping tablets, the glass of milk — looked with perfect submission into my eyes. I knew that the immortality I had conferred on the poor fellow was a slippery sophism, a play upon words. But the very last lap of his life had been happy and it had been proven to him that death was b